My 78 project bus has some strange electrical things going on with the fuel
injection system and I know that after testing everything else you should
look into changing out the electrical control unit. I don't want to invest
in it unless I have a pretty good idea this is the problem.

I have good fuel pressure and spark at every plug. The AFC unit seems in
working order and turns the fuel pump on when the flap is opened and there
is power to the fuel injectors, but no spray???
